====Usage notes====
The adjectives {{m|en|nonhuman}}, {{m|en|inhuman}}, and {{m|en|unhuman}} have [[connotation#Noun|connotative]] and [[denotation#Noun|denotative]] differences. The word {{m|en|nonhuman}} is usually a neutrally toned adjective referring to any animals or other life forms that are not humans. The word {{m|en|inhuman}} is usually an emotionally charged word conveying an idea of [[inhumaneness]], [[cruelty]], emotional [[coldness]], or [[uncanniness]]. The word {{m|en|unhuman}} is less common and usually means the same as {{m|en|inhuman}}.

